values: Im sorry. Im sorry I cant be your perfect little angel. That Im not just like her or him. Sometimes that Im not him, but its not like I can help that. I know things would be different then too. But Im just too damn sick of trying. Because nothing ends up working in the end anyways. Go figure.

O god o god o god. It all just clicked. Yeah it only took a day. O god no. Thats not supossed to happen. No no no no no. Its not going to be for awhile, but still, doesnt make it any easier or better. Please be alright. I dont want anything bad to happen.

O how I loathe early Saturday rehersals. No one sane should be up at 7 on a Saturday. But yet I was. And o it was long. But Erin gave me my giant ass gumball, so I twas occupied for most of the time. God I love those things. Then walked up to Subway with Er, in the POURING RAIN and through the FLOOODED FIELD. God we were so soaked when we got there. But we were hungry, so who cares? Then back to the school to pain the signs since NO ONE stayed at all *glares* But twas mucho fun and all the such.

Got home, went out with mine daddy for a bit, got dinner. Listened to the drunk people downstairs who were starting a stunning karyoke game. God it was like 5:00 and this guys were just drunk out of their minds. O my god it was like the funniest thing ever. 

Home again, home again. Watched The Notebook. That movies really good, but its just so sad and sweet. I think theres a reason I stay away from those kinds of movies. Because you know that sort of thing only can happen in movies. Twas good all the same though. But now I do feel rather sad from it.


Oy. I do not know what is going on with my mind. Do make it stop. Tis too confuseling :\

Only 1 day of break left...

1. I love Queer Eye.

5. Compliment me. 
4. Talk to me.
3. Be spontanious. Ok I know I spelled that wrong.
2. Laugh at me.
1. Corniness is cute.


EIGHT things I want to do before I die:
8. Go to Europe.
7. Make something of myself.
6. Get married.
5. Have some fun times. hehe
4. Climb that damn rock wall lol.
3. Eat an entire Ben and Jerrys ice cream thingy.
2. Meet someone famous.
1. Not be forgotten.

4. Dont listen to me.

2. Be incredibly snooty and think youre better than I am.
1. Not being yourself.

1. Love.

1. Not living life to the fullest.

4. My bed 
3. My awesome chair
2. All the stuff on my walls.
1. The phone

THREE things I do everyday:
3. Listen to music
2. Shower
1. Umm wear underwear lol

TWO things I want to do right now:
2. Eat dinner
1. Go out somewhere.

ONE person I want to see right now:
1. Erin. She has something for me lol.


O bored am I, I am. I know I  know, everyones just taking notes about what I wrote there. 

Gooda day today. I heart my 80s music. It makes everything betterer.

She's beautiful as usual 
With bruises on her ego and 
Her killer instinct tells her to
Beware of evil men 


It was a Sugarcult kind of day today. That song kinda describes my mentality at the moment, not that anyone cares but hey Im letting you know anyways.

Rehersal today was only 3 hours instead of 5. Weee. Thank god. Got home and then went on an adventure to Jons Video with Sar. Interesting I do say.

And now I sit on my ass by myself for another nite. Woo. So exciting.
Could I be any more of a total fuck up?

So spent pretty much all of last nite and today with Abbeh. Fun times, fun times. I do heart her so.

Got home, cleaned stuff up a little, almost managed to burn my finger off quite a few times. I have such great skill.

Came downstairs to basically 'hey we hate our daughter'. My mum leaves again tomorrow, I dont know if I can take living with my dad again, he was home for all of 2 seconds today before we started screaming at each other. Fun stuff there.


*She gets sad when there's nothing going on, yeah
She says it makes her feel damn worthless


And now. Just feel like crappo. Damn worthless to say so. But some things will do that to you. Trying not to believe its the hard part though.

Science magazine came out with a report on the difference   
between men and women's brains. Apparently women are more   
controlled by a part of the brain called singletgyrus.   

Men are more controlled by a part of the brain known as the   
penis.   


Hahaha Well I thought it was funny...


It always seems like the questions that you dont ask are the only ones that get answered. But the reason you never asked them to begin with is because you dont want to know the answer, or else its already clear... 

I just need to shut off my brain. Life would be so much easier then.

Hum de dum de dum what a day. Went shopping with the madre for like all of the afternoon. Unfortunatly twas all just for the wedding, but I will never argue about spending an hour in DSW to find shoes. But I did find shoes, and theyre so adorable, theyre black with white polka dots, ahh I love them so. Then we went to the mall to grab some stuff and it was just so freaking packed that it was annoying. All the agressive stroller driver ladies geez. Got home and chilled for a little then went over to Sars to babysit her brother haha I love that kid hes too funny. Did the entire freaking bio packet though. And was supossed to be watching the incredibly fun and interesting Spongebob Squarepants Movie, but texting Matt was just so much more interesting lol. But what I saw of the movie, was....hahaha interesting, but it was funny, which could be kinda sad. And now am hoping to go to Erins and gift and hang out and the such. O la de da happy mood.

So, went out with Kaylee for a bit today. Fun stuff. But we should never do grocery shopping. O dear that was rather scary. Came home and hung out for awhile, but then my sugar high began to wear off and that kinda sucked. So went to take a bath, turned up my Goos really high and sung along loudly and probably out of key sometimes, but who cares, since I couldnt really hear me anyways. O but it felt nice, its such a good way to destressanize yournself. 

And now I am home to watch my Friday nite standup and such.

Gah, I really wish my head would just stop...thinking. Its making everything so confusing.

Today was actually quite good for the most part. Even though it was raining, but I guess I never really got to look outside, so that rather helped. 

Its odd, things that used to completely ruin my day, now just seem to roll of my back. They just never seem to click right away thankfully. But at the same time things that never made me look twice now bother me more than ever. 

Aw, one of the little kids at rehersal just made my day though. He was sitting next to his sister and turned to her and was like "Wait, how are we supossed to sit down in a kilt?" God I have no idea why I thought that to be so funny, but it rather was, it was just so cute. 

I read this quote today that just seemd really true to life. I kinda had one of those cheesy inspirational moments reading it. 

No matter how qualified or deserving we are, we will never   
reach a better life until we can imagine it for ourselves   
and allow ourselves to have it.   
--Richard Bach

It kinda makes me think.


*Whatever tomorrow brings...

O what another charming day today was. But my mum finally came home tonite. I dont think Ive ever been happier to see her than today. My dad has just had a stick up his ass this week or something.

I realized a bit today. That I dont fit into drama. Everyone has their own cliques, but I just dont belong there. No one really talks to me, so yeah I guess its great I get to get some of my homwork done. Yeah. Right. I guess I realized alot about who it is that really does care about me. Like the people that think I might exist. And that list keeps getting shorter. What is happening to me? Im just fading away from everything it seems. Maybe Ill just end up disapearing eventually. Glad to feel just so cared about. Thanks.

Today was such a Monday. And of course I wanted to stay up later last nite to watch part of the Roast of Jeff Foxworthy, so I was more tired today, especially since I didnt get to catch up on sleep this weekend.

Id forgotten how nice it felt to feel special. All it really takes is a simple hello if Im not looking so good or actually pretending that you care. Lately Ive just been fading into the background of everyone and everything it seems like. Im sorry Im not as awesome as everyone else, but you wouldnt know if you didnt bother to talk to me now would you? Im so sick of shit. And then feeling bad because I have my own. It happens. And seeing the large amount of comments I always get on bad days, maybe that shows something too. Come on, make me smile people. I dunno, everythings just turning grey.  

Only 2 more days. God I need break.

So today was pretty freaking awesome. Last nite went up to Potomac Pizza to  meet Er and have pizza obviously. Got in a big fight with the padre, so my mood managed to suck when I got in there, but good company and good food improved that. Went home with her and Kaylee came over too. Watched Pirates of the Caribbean and fell asleep. No problems there, Johnny Depp and Orlando Bloom are two faces I deffinatly dont mind falling asleep to :) Got up early and Alex and Tara came over and we went to brunch? at this really awesome restaraunt in DC. Mmmm sooo yummy. Then went to see RENT. Ahhh omg it was so incredibly amazing. Thats probably all I can really say about it. It made Kelly very happy. So yes, rather good day.

Ew back to school tomorrow. But only 3 day week for moi. Heck yes.

la de da de da. Ooo its so pretty out. Im deffinatly ready for it to be spring. 

Rehersals at 8 suck, but it was awesome. Feet hurt rather much now, but hey hey. So then after about 3 hours of lots of standing, stayed around to help Erin with signs and stuff. Twas fun. On a mucho sugar high from eating those conversation hearts. Woo de do de do. 

Yeah, I know I rather avoid the subject unlike the rest of the world. But all Im trying to do is keep spirits up right now.

Ooo spring weather improves the mood o so much :)

School on Friday suckkss. So does long rehersal on Fridays. I deffinatly cant be still for that long, I was feeling so ADD.

So then got home and had a total freak attack. I dont think I can take living with my dad for too much longer, its going to drive me nuts. Everything is just in a total mess, I can not stand it. Hes a total freaking slob and cant do a damn thing to help with anything. I dont wanna be taking care of a house, Im freaking 15 years old.

But then I had mac n cheese and then a Snickers that I stole from my little cousin, and I calmed down quite a bit.

Seems like its going to be yet another watch movies and comedy nite. Theres a shocker. My Friday nites are so predictable. O how I wish I didnt have to be at the school at 8 tomorrow. That royally bites.



And she wonders where these dreams go
'Cause the world got in her way
What's the point in ever trying
Nothing's changing anyway

Ug I wish things could change. That it wasnt the same crap all the time. That maybe something would. That I could stop being a shadow to everyone, that you would actually look at me instead of through me, that maybe something overly good would happen. But nothing is changing. Im sick of trying.

Woo. So today was St. Patricks Day. Except it kinda killed the Irish thing when someone told me that St. Patrick was really British. Damn.
  
Ug. Lunch sucked today. I opened Erins locker to put something in it and her Snapple lept out at me and broke. I felt so horribly bad, and everyone kept looking at me. YES, god I fucking broke it, so stop staring at me, I already felt bad enough. Then spent the rest of the time doing spanish homework that I thought was due today, but I found out it wasnt due til tomorrow when I was like finished. Gaah, that was no fun.

Ug, Im so sick of being living background for everything. I mean geez, wether or not you acknowledge that Im alive doesnt change the fact that Im here. Im tired of just being a shadow of everyone.

Why is it hardest to grab the attention of the person you want it most from? Arg.

I love this song.

to get it right

to maybe find someone

Its a rather true song if you really hear it.


I dunno, I suppose today could be considered better. 

St. Patricks Day tomorrow. Probably need to find something that is green. That could be good to do.

Gah, I fell asleep during chem while we were going over the review for the test tomorrow. God my timing sucks.

Long rehersals blooow.

I really need to get more sleep. I dont know why I always end up being so tired, it doesnt help anything.

Its just been one of those days. That everything goes fine until you get home and youre by yourself. Theres no one left there to impress but yourself, and you already know yourself well enough that theres no need for impression. That all you can do is sit and think, zoning out to whatever it is thats on the tv for backgroud noise, because the silence will just make it worse. But you just sit and think. Think about how everything is going. Think about the day and days gone past and the days to come. The days past are the worst, because those you cant change, and the days to come are frightening because you dont know what it is that can happen. Sit and think about what life brings. Theres always the good things, friendship, love, that sudden feeling when everything just clicks. But at the same time everything seems overshadowed by the bad. The broken fights, the tears cried when you think everyones backs are turned and no one can see you, the feeling of being so alone and no one caring. The need to hide everything from everyone. Because you have to be fine. But nothing ever works out that way. You just have to smile through it all. Put up a lie on your face for the world to see and try to make them believe that lie because you need to try and believe it too.

So last nite was interesting. My family is so odd. They were having a conversation about breasts at the dinner table. Because they had chicken and apparently it was a small chicken. "Well maybe this chicken had a DD and they just got cut in half?" "Yeah but if you cut a DD in half youd get at least a B" Omg what is wrong with my family?

And today was not the swellest of days. I figure if I get ignored more I can drop off the face of the earth. Hey hey, doesnt sound so bad.

I almost got hit in the head with a roll of flying toilet paper today. That was interesting. 

Ug. I didnt know it was so difficault to look the other way and pretend you never noticed. I dont know if itll be better or worse when the year ends though.


*And no matter how hard I try 
I can't escape these things inside I know*

O another dull Sunday. But havent killed the small cousin yet, so I guess thats a good sign. 

Its odd, for the past 2 days, Ive felt like I need to keep myself busy. Well, I kinda understand why, but Im running out of things to do. And thats not so good.


I just dunno.


Everythings so blurry.

Ooooo what a good day. Went shopping with Steph, bought a ton of stuff, and just chilled at the mall for like 4 hours lol. Went back to her house for a bit and hung out there too, looked at yearbook schtuff. Good times Steph, good times. Then me dad picked me up and brought me back to the hell hole. But the car ride was really fun. Listened to Marley, which apparently he has. I kinda felt like I was riding in the stoner mobile though lol, but it was awesome. Twas surprised how much I really do have in common with him, kinda odd to realize things. But then twas home and the annoying cousin is of course here. I swear I may end up killing him before tomorrow. And then just been busy all tonite. Like I dunno, I havent been able to sit still, Ive needed to keep busy since I got home, and I have. It was actually really nice. 

Gaah I just feel so awesome :) Good days and lots of shopping do that :)

COEUR D'ALENE, Idaho - How do you get back at someone who   
puts peanut butter in your cheese sandwich? Well, you   
anonymously send them semen-frosted brownies, of course! A   
17-year-old student admitted to sending the brownies to a   
fellow student, who then shared the sweets with two other   
teens. The guilty party told a school resource officer that   
he was upset about the peanut butter prank, explaining that   
"he hated peanut butter and it made him more mad than he   
could explain," according to the police report. The student   
was arrested and booked into a juvenile detention center.   
The victims of the disgusting prank were tested for anything   
that might have been transmitted through the body fluid. 

God people are so strange. 

Ug so I woke up this morning and the first thing I see/hear going downstairs is the small cousin. O lord help me. So incredibly glad Im getting out of here today.

Ahhhh I feel like 82374329870987234 times better :) I just took this looong bath, turned the water up about as hot as it would go, and put in my Our Lady Peace cd. Which I turned up about as loud as I figured I could without being yelled at. And sung along as loud as possible of course. Gaaah what is it about baths that just make everything so much better? 

Except one thing of course...But that cant be changed.

Still not all in the right, but hey, whatcha gonna do? Been feeling all creative like lately, odd again. And even writing stuff. I know, doesnt it amaze you?

Ooo so I am back from the glorious Boston. It was really damn fun. Went shopping with me aunt on Monday. It was so awesome, since I was like the only person in the stores, except for the ladies that think theyre still juniors but theyre not. So they go shopping during the day so that no one else sees them shopping there except the other age confused women. But other than them, I was like the only person there. And all the people were looking at me all weird since it looked like I was skipping school, which I wasnt since school really was canceled here too. But the guy at the Pac Sun was really hot, so it was all good :) Aaand I got these incredibly awesome NEON ORANGE Chucks. O theyre so awesome, so that day was so good. And flew home Tuesday. I looove flying at nite. Its the prettiest thing ever to look down on the cities at nite. The lights look like sequins on some ladies black velvet dress. I dunno, thats the only way I can think to call it. I know, I just have this way with words. 

But now Im back in the o so wonderful Poolesville. Ug. I really wish that I was back in Boston. I didnt have to wake up and put on a happy face, because I really was happy. I cant ever remember times Im more happy then when Im there. Theres nothing to worry about up there. But of course I had to come back and realize that theres still a world here. Wonderful. I wish the world would just completely disapear, its not like theres anything worth it left in it. And I dunno, that might sound pessimistic to some people, but I really think that thats true to me. I dunno, it just seems that when I get back everything seems to hit me all at once, and I dont want it. Any of it. Im not back into everything yet. I just want to enjoy everything for now, but I cant. Ug, make the world go away.

Most people got married in June because they took their   
yearly bath in Mary and still smelled pretty good. However,   
they were starting to smell, which is why brides carried a   
bouquet of flowers to hide the body odor.   

Baths consisted of a big tub of hot water. The man of the   
house had the nice clean water, then, all the other sons and   
men, then the women and, finally, the children. By then, the   
water was so dirty you could actually lose someone in it -   
hence the saying, "Don't throw the baby out with the bath-   
water."   

Houses had thatched roofs - thick straw, piled high, with no   
wood underneath. It was the only place for animals to get   
warm, so all the dogs, cats, and other small animals lived   
in the roof. When it rained, it became slippery and sometimes   
the animals would slide off the roof. Hence the saying, "It's   
raining cats and dogs."   

There was nothing to stop things from falling into the house.   
Bugs and other droppings could really mess up your clean bed.   
Hence, a bed with big posts and a sheet hung over the top   
afforded some protection. That's how canopy beds came into   
existence.   

Sometimes folks could obtain pork, which made them feel   
quite special. When visitors came over, they would hang up   
their bacon to show off. It was a sign of wealth that a man   
could "bring home the bacon."   

Those with money had plates made of pewter. Food with a high   
acid content caused some of the lead to leach onto the food,   
causing lead poisoning and death. This happened most often   
with tomatoes, so for the next 400 years or so, tomatoes   
were considered poisonous.      

Lead cups were used to drink ale or whiskey. The combination   
would sometimes knock people out for a couple of days. Some-   
one walking along the road would take them for dead and   
prepare them for burial. The person would be laid out on the   
kitchen table for a couple of days and the family would   
gather around and wait to see if he or she would wake up -   
hence the custom of holding a "wake."
